citeinfo.title: VILLAGES OF MALAWI
citeinfo.othercit: Users noting corrections or additions to this map are requested to annotate and send them to the Surveyor General P. O. Box 349, Blantyre, MALAWI.

descript.abstract: This POINT feature for the 10 sheets of 1;250,000 series, created by DNLMMP as national reference data sets for 250,000 topographic series.
descript.purpose: To be used for GIS analysis at 1:250000 scale and smaller.

timeperd.current: The basis on which the time period of content information is determined. REQUIRED.

idinfo.useconst: To be by the buyer only. NOT for reselll. The Surveyor General is only one who sells these data sets.

horizpa.horizpar: This could the most accurate data for villages in Malawi. Since was created from village point coordinates.

srcinfo.typesrc: Village Cordinates from an Atlass of Malawi produced by Surveys Department

procstep.procdesc: The Village names and coordinates were scanned and as text by OCR (Optical Character Recognition) facility of HP IRIS Cleaning of the data was done in ESRI ArcInfo 8.0.2. The shapefile was made by ArcView 3.2
